From fe47e3a9dc4a8fcce5bd860888d7d99d6b546683 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joakim Bech <joakim.bech@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2026 12:15:01 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Disable mnist-rs example due to Rust 1.86 incompatibility
 with zune-jpeg

The zune-jpeg crate 0.5.12 uses #[target_feature(enable = "neon")]
on non-unsafe functions, which became a hard error in Rust 1.86.
Remove mnist-rs example which depends on image crate that depends on zune-jpeg.
